title.narrative: By 2021, Government partners have increased technical and management capacity to provide high impact child and maternal nutritionservices

description.narrative: Between January and September 2021 through UNICEF support a total of 813,441 beneficiaries were effectively reached with high-impact, cost-effective child and maternal nutrition services including: lifesaving therapeutic services for children with severe acute malnutrition (SAM) and moderate acute malnutrition (MAM) in communities and facilities; supplementation of vitamin A, iron, folic acid and iodine to control and eliminate micronutrient deficiency disorders; and maternal, infant and young child nutrition (MIYCN) counselling services.;;; | Status:Met | As-of Date:23/12/2021
